## 5. Network Protocol — Complete Wire Format

### 5.1 The Single Streaming Endpoint

**Everything flows through one POST request:**

```
POST https://gemini.google.com/_/BardChatUi/data/assistant.lamda.BardFrontendService/StreamGenerate
```

**Query parameters:**

| Param | Example | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `bl` | `boq_assistant-bard-web-server_20260408.07_p0` | Build label, changes with deployments |
| `f.sid` | `-293394717459457665` | Session ID, stable per browser session |
| `hl` | `en` | Language |
| `_reqid` | `8967491` | Incrementing request ID |
| `rt` | `c` | Response type flag |

**Request headers of note:**

| Header | Value/Purpose |
|---|---|
| `content-type` | `application/x-www-form-urlencoded;charset=UTF-8` |
| `x-goog-ext-525001261-jspb` | Contains the **image generation ID** as a JSPB array: `[1,null,null,null,"e051ce1aa80aa576",null,null,0,,null,null,2]` |
| `x-same-domain` | `1` |

**Response headers:**

| Header | Value |
|---|---|
| `content-type` | `application/json; charset=utf-8` |
| `content-disposition` | `attachment; filename="response.bin"` |
| `content-encoding` | `gzip` |

### 5.2 Response Wire Format — Chunked Length-Prefixed JSON

The response body is **NOT** standard JSON and **NOT** Server-Sent Events. It is a proprietary **length-prefixed chunked format**:

```
)]}'

{byte_count}
{JSON_array}
{byte_count}
{JSON_array}
...
```

- Starts with the anti-XSSI prefix `)]}'\n\n`
- Each chunk: a **decimal byte count** on its own line, followed by a JSON array on the next line(s)
- All chunks are wrapped in `[["wrb.fr", ...]]` envelope

### 5.3 Stream Chunk Sequence — Thinking Mode (Image Generation)

The chunks arrive in this **exact order**:

---

**Chunk 1 — Session initialization:**
```json
[["wrb.fr",null,"[null,[null,\"r_67d33de905ac70d7\"],{\"18\":\"r_67d33de905ac70d7\",\"21\":[\"GkM-427RUtQN...\"],\"44\":false}]"]]
```
- `r_67d33de905ac70d7` = **response ID**
- Key `"18"` = response ID assignment
- Key `"44"` = false throughout (unknown flag)

---

**Chunks 2–4 — "Creating your image..." status (repeated):**
```json
[["wrb.fr",null,"[null,[\"c_109e00563eac533e\",\"r_67d33de905ac70d7\"],{\"7\":[null,[\"data_analysis_tool\",[null,null,\"Creating your image...\"],1,[null,[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,],false]],null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,[]],\"44\":false}]"]]
```
- `c_109e00563eac533e` = **conversation ID**
- Key `"7"` contains tool invocation: `"data_analysis_tool"` with message `"Creating your image..."`
- The `1` or `4` after the message is a **status code** (alternates — likely progress state)
- `` = image generation tool type identifier

---

**Chunk 5 — Thinking header update (CoT indicator in stream):**
```json
[["wrb.fr",null,"[null,[\"c_109e00563eac533e\",\"r_67d33de905ac70d7\"],{\"7\":[null,null,null,null,null,[\"Constructing the Image\"],null,null,null,[\"Show Thinking (Nano Banana 2)\",\"Hide Thinking (Nano Banana 2)\"],null,[]],\"44\":false}]"]]
```
- Key `"7"`, index `` = **current thinking step title** (e.g., `"Constructing the Image"`)
- Key `"7"`, index `` = **UI toggle labels**: `["Show Thinking (Nano Banana 2)","Hide Thinking (Nano Banana 2)"]`
- **`"Nano Banana 2"` is the model label** — extract this
- **This chunk only appears when thinking mode is active** — its presence = `thinking_mode = 1`

---

**Chunk 6 — The massive payload (~13KB+):**

This is the main response chunk. Its inner JSON (after unescaping the string value in `wrb.fr`) contains **everything**:

#### 6a. Input Image Reference
Located in the nested array under key `"46"` within the candidate metadata:

```json
[null, 1, "0b62bc10fa6e61a6_DSC_0428.jpg",
 "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gg/AMW1TPqQcPcH...",
 null, "$AQ34dajZit304BQs...",
 null, null, 1,
 [1775897905, 247072000],
 null, "image/jpeg",
 null, null, null,
 [1024, 682, 196182]]
```

| Index | Value | Meaning |
|---|---|---|
| `` | `"0b62bc10fa6e61a6_DSC_0428.jpg"` | **Original filename** (prefixed with upload hash) |
| `` | `"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gg/..."` | **Google-hosted URL** of uploaded input image |
| `` | `[1775897905, 247072000]` | **Timestamp** (seconds, nanoseconds) |
| `` | `"image/jpeg"` | **MIME type** |
| `` | `[1024, 682, 196182]` | **Width, Height, file size in bytes** |

The original filename is extractable: strip everything before the first `_` → `DSC_0428.jpg`.

#### 6b. Chain-of-Thought (Thinking Text)
Located deep in the candidate response array. The CoT appears in **two formats** within the same chunk:

**Format A — Concatenated markdown string:**
A single escaped string containing the full CoT with `**Bold Headers**` and `\n\n` separators:

```
"**Analyzing the Image's Details**\n\nI'm currently focusing on dissecting..."
```

**Format B — Structured array of individual thought steps:**
Each step is a separate array element with metadata:

```json
[null,[null,0,"Analyzing the Image's Details",[[0,29,[[null,null,null,null,2]]]]]]
```

| Position | Content | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `` | `"Analyzing the Image's Details"` | Text content |
| `` | `[[0,29,[[null,null,null,null,2]]]]` | Formatting metadata: `[0,29]` = bold range (chars 0–29), `2` = bold style |

Steps **alternate** between headers (with bold formatting metadata) and body paragraphs (no formatting metadata):

```json
// Header step:
[null,[null,0,"Analyzing the Image's Details",[[0,29,[[null,null,null,null,2]]]]]]
// Body step:
[null,[null,0,"I'm currently focusing on dissecting the original image..."]]
// Header step:
[null,[null,0,"Mapping Contrast and Elements",[[0,29,[[null,null,null,null,2]]]]]]
// Body step:
[null,[null,0,"I'm now zeroing in on deconstructing..."]]
```

**Thinking detection rule:** If the structured thought array exists and contains entries → `thinking_mode = 1`. The **concatenated markdown string** (Format A) is what to store in `thinking_text`.

The CoT is wrapped inside a tool response structure:
```
[[[""],""," file_content_fetcher_tool","",[]],
 [["**Analyzing..."],  // Format A
  "","","",
  [[[step1],[step2],...]]  // Format B
 ]]
```

The tool name `"file_content_fetcher_tool"` wraps the thinking output.

#### 6c. Output Images
Located in a nested structure under what appears to be image generation results:

```json
[null,null,null,
  [null,1,"732743932528795549.png",
   "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gg-dl/AOI_d_8DlqWZ7N...",
   null,"$AQ34dahSD2yRv24FL...",
   null,null,2,
   [1775897939,168101940],
   null,"image/png",
   null,null,null,
   [1264,842,1201186]],
  null,null,
  [null,1,"6061769919743100983.jpeg",
   "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gg-dl/AOI_d_8vei4YtNg...",
   null,"$AQ34dai1D+XeojxK8...",
   null,null,2,
   [1775897939,167971320],
   null,"image/jpeg",
   null,null,null,
   [1264,842,493090]]
]
```

| Field | Image 1 (PNG) | Image 2 (JPEG) |
|---|---|---|
| Filename | `732743932528795549.png` | `6061769919743100983.jpeg` |
| URL prefix | `AOI_d_` (via `gg-dl/`) | `AOI_d_` (via `gg-dl/`) |
| Dimensions | `1264 × 842` | `1264 × 842` |
| File size | `1,201,186` bytes (~1.2MB) | `493,090` bytes (~493KB) |
| MIME | `image/png` | `image/jpeg` |

The **PNG is the full-quality output**. The **JPEG is the compressed preview/alternate**. Output image URLs follow this pattern and are later fetched as separate network requests (`AOI_d_*=s1024-rj?alr=yes`).

The `=s1024` suffix controls served resolution. Replace with `=s128` for 128px thumbnail.

#### 6d. Synthetic Prompt (What Gemini Actually Sent to Imagen)
A fully expanded English prompt is embedded:

```
"A high-resolution, precise digital Photoshop contrast-adjustment mask based on
<IMAGE_0>. The image is rendered as a pixel-perfect mask with a pure black background
representing neutral (no contrast change). Elements to have increased contrast are
rendered in pure, solid magenta (255, 0, 255). These magenta areas precisely
correspond to: all the individual spherical shapes of the red grapes; solid shapes
for the large, flat, geometric top surfaces of all the diced watermelon cubes..."
```

This is the **model-rewritten prompt** — the actual instruction sent to the image generation backend. Valuable to store for debugging generation quality.

#### 6e. Model Label
Found in two places:
- The thinking toggle chunk: `"Show Thinking (Nano Banana 2)"`
- The final payload: `"Nano Banana 2"` as a standalone string near the end

#### 6f. Safety Classifier Results
An array of classifier names and results is embedded (useful for understanding rejections):

```json
["gempix2_thinking_mode_input_regex",[null,[true]]]
["public_entity_ungrounded_sup_classifier",[...]]
["text_safety_classifier",[...]]
["image_and_video_safety_classifier",[...]]
["gempix_reactive_safety_classifier",[...]]
["input_prompt_regex",[...]]
["output_prompt_regex",[...]]
```

The key `"gempix2_thinking_mode_input_regex"` with value `[null,[true]]` is another **binary thinking-mode indicator**.

#### 6g. Image Content Labels
An array of classification labels with confidence scores from the output image:

```json
[["Human action","/m/07p82rh",0.93911326],
 ["Photograph","/m/068jd",0.9340232],
 ["Grapes","/m/0d_4s",0.6604252],
 ["Fruit","/m/02xwb",0.3510264], ...]
```

---

**Chunk 7 — Prompt echo:**
```json
[["wrb.fr",null,"[null,[\"c_109e00563eac533e\",\"r_67d33de905ac70d7\"],{\"11\":[\"Turn this into a photoshop mask, pure magenta where the contrast is increased and pure green where the contrast is decreased. +contrast melon edges, flats of watermelon, strawberry seeds, grapes. -contrast strawberry greens, serving plate.\"],\"44\":false}]"]]
```
- Key `"11"` = **the original user prompt text as an array with one string element**
- This is the clean, unmodified prompt exactly as typed

---

**Chunk 8 — Session token:**
```json
[["wrb.fr",null,"[null,[\"c_109e00563eac533e\",\"r_67d33de905ac70d7\"],{\"26\":\"AwAAAAAAAAAg4DUFz3Xz2P6f8UG81xlM72BiXKdQZhMAAAA\",\"44\":false}]"]]
```
- Key `"26"` = session continuation token (base64)

---

**Chunk 9 — Termination:**
```json
[["di",38706],["af.httprm",38705,"-6436033568662573789",42]]
```
```json
[["e",19,null,null,157032]]
```
- `"di"` = final byte offset
- `"af.httprm"` = HTTP request metadata cleanup
- `"e"` = end signal, `157032` = total response size in bytes

