## 10. Extension Architecture

| Component | File | Responsibility |
|---|---|---|
| Service Worker | `background.js` | Intercepts `StreamGenerate` via `chrome.webRequest` or `chrome.debugger`, routes parsed data to offscreen |
| Content Script | `content.js` | Minimal — only needed if DOM interaction required (e.g., fallback blob capture) |
| Offscreen Document | `offscreen.html` + `offscreen.js` | Canvas for 128px resize, sql.js for SQLite, fetch for image downloads |
| Popup | `popup.html` + `popup.js` | DB export button, row count, basic stats |

**Critical implementation note:** The StreamGenerate response must be intercepted as a **full response body** — it is **not** an EventSource stream. It returns as a regular `application/json` POST response with the chunked length-prefix format described above. Use `chrome.debugger` with `Network.getResponseBody` or a `DeclarativeNetRequest` + response body interception pattern. The `chrome.webRequest` API in MV3 **cannot read response bodies** — this is the primary technical constraint.
